==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nonjuror
<hw>Non*ju"ror</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eng. Hist.)</fld>
<def>One of those adherents of <person>James II.</person> who refused to
take the oath of allegiance to William and Mary, or to their successors,
after the revolution of 1688; a Jacobite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonjurorism</ent>⟦br⟧
